  "response": "The situation involving former President Donald Trump and former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton is complex and highly political. As of my last update in October 2023, there had been no indication from Trump regarding any specific plans to offer a pardon to Clinton or any intent to \"let the clock run out\" on a potential pardon. \n\nPardons are a significant aspect of a president's powers, and any action taken by Trump or discussions about a pardon would likely be influenced by political strategy, public opinion, and legal considerations. Additionally, the pardon power typically applies to federal offenses and does not extend to state-level charges.\n\nSince this topic involves speculation about political maneuvers, it\u2019s important to stay updated with reliable news sources for the latest developments.",
